Licensed Work Components and Use Provisions

I. LICENSED WORK COMPONENTS
   The Licensed Work "Diggers V1" refers to the entire invention and logic of
   the protocol, including the deployed contracts, the interfaces, the
   libraries, and the documentation, which includes but is not limited to:

   A. CORE SMART CONTRACTS:
      1. Diggers (the singleton launchpad: factory + swap router + Uniswap V4
         unlock-callback host + fee splitter + name registry)
      2. DiggersToken (the launched-coin implementation; every launch is an
         EIP-1167 minimal proxy of it)
      3. DiggersCoin ($DIG, the platform coin and buy-mining airdrop)
      4. DiggersRouter (the universal V2/V3/V4 fee router for rescued tokens)

   B. PROTOCOL LIBRARIES:
      1. DiggerCharset
      2. DiggerCreateLib
      3. DiggerGraduationLib
      4. DiggerGraduationMath
      5. DiggerHarvestLib
      6. DiggerHarvestMath
      7. DiggerHarvestViews
      8. DiggerLaunchLiquidity
      9. DiggerLaunchMath
      10. DiggerMath
      11. DiggerQuotes
      12. DiggerRegistryLib
      13. DiggerSwapViews
      14. DiggerV4

   C. PROTOCOL INTERFACES:
      1. IDiggers
      2. IDiggersToken
      3. IDiggersCoin
      4. IDiggersRouter

   D. OFFICIAL DEPLOYED CONTRACT ADDRESSES:
      The canonical addresses of the official Diggers V1 deployment (the
      Diggers launchpad, the DiggersToken implementation, the DiggersCoin
      $DIG token, and the DiggersRouter), together with the chains they are
      deployed on, are published as ENS text records at
      v1-deployments.diggersdotfun.eth. Only addresses published there are
      official; every other deployment of this code is a counterfeit.

II. AUTHORIZED USES
    Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the Licensor hereby
    grants the Licensee the following rights:

    A. The Licensee may launch coins through the official Diggers deployment,
       trade them, harvest fees, graduate them, reserve names, and earn money
       from all of these activities.

    B. The Licensee may build interfaces, applications, bots, and tools that
       interact with the official Diggers deployment and earn money from such
       activities.

    C. The Licensee may develop smart contracts of any kind that interact
       with the official Diggers deployment and earn money from such
       development.

    D. The Licensee may integrate existing protocols and platforms with the
       official Diggers deployment and earn money from such integration.

    E. The Licensee may build on top of coins launched through the official
       Diggers deployment (including their points, daily contest, vesting,
       and graduation mechanics) and earn money from such expansion.

    F. The Licensee may index, display, analyze, and redistribute on-chain
       data emitted by the official Diggers deployment and earn money from
       such services.

    G. The Licensee may deploy smart contracts, platforms, or tools that
       reference the official Diggers addresses published at
       v1-deployments.diggersdotfun.eth, provided they preserve those
       addresses and do not alter or bypass the protocol's intended
       functionality or security measures, and may earn money from such
       deployment.

III. PROHIBITED USES
     Notwithstanding any other provisions of this License, the Licensee is
     expressly prohibited from:

     A. Any uses not listed in Section II above.

     B. Forking the deployed contracts.

     C. Deploying their own identical or customized version of Diggers V1.

     D. Deploying their own identical or customized version of Diggers V1 or
        its logic rewritten in another programming language.

     E. Deploying Diggers V1 on any chain not listed at
        v1-deployments.diggersdotfun.eth.

     F. Using the Diggers name, logo, or branding without permission.

     G. Earning money by deploying their own version of Diggers V1.

     H. Earning money by using Diggers V1 on chains not listed at
        v1-deployments.diggersdotfun.eth.

     I. Earning money by deploying their identical or customized version of
        Diggers V1.

     J. Modifying, altering, or replacing the official addresses published at
        v1-deployments.diggersdotfun.eth in any implementation, or creating
